{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-8423].
  {panel}

When replacing the default JIRA logo, it causes the text of the URL in the page header to disappear.  (In your default instance, this is set to "Atlassian JIRA".)  I can tell that this is not a font color problem, because highlighting the area shows that it is just a single blank space.

We have a small enough logo that it would be nice to keep the URL at the top of the page.  I checked out the instance used on the Jakarta project, and they seem to have the same issue.

When SAPDb/MaxDB is used, JIRA apparently reports the following 

{noformat}
2005-11-03 15:22:23,052 DEBUG [atlassian.jira.upgrade.ConsistencyCheckImpl] File >entityengine.xml is configured to use 'sapdb' but there is no known mapping for this field type.
{noformat}

We should update the list of known database/driver mappings.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-8387].
  {panel}

I had a bunch of issues in a component that I wanted to version. So I needed to move them to a new project for just that component. The bulk move worked fine, but the bulk edit to change the version would not work because a good number of the issues were closed. The bulk operations should be able to bulk edit the status or bulk edit the version information, even when the issues are closed.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-8385].
  {panel}

When iterating over many development builds, each with their own roadmap for internal use / "XP" style short cycle development, it would be very useful to get a nice printout of all the issues in a specific version - i.e. a Roadmap for a single version, without any of the other Jira options shown on the page and the current status of all the issues in that version.

These can then be pasted up on the wall in your office so people know what is (or will be) in each build.

Currently it's a bit awkward getting this info out of jira nicely to a printer.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-8376].
  {panel}

See JRA-7403

Our Jira server isnt configured to be "public" - this is so users only see the projects that interest them.

However, we want trackbacks to work.

Bug report from Peter Ridge

When running through the CSV Importer we need to make sure that fields with a dot in the title are correctly processed as a date field. Currently it seems to only store the part of the field name after the dot.

e.g. The date field {{Eng. Acceptance Date}} is being stored as:

{code}
date.fields =  Acceptance Date
{code}

When a workflow has a step with no outgoing transitions (eg. 'Closed' with no 'Reopen'), then issues in this step will be flagged as broken by the integrity checker:

{noformat}
Check workflow current step entries
   ERROR: 	ABC-2711 - The workflow entry with id 239344 does not have a corresponding current step. 	JRA-4539
{noformat}

There is nothing wrong with such issues. We should either fix the check or remove it altogether.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-8368].
  {panel}

When adding a version on the 'Manage Versions' page, one enters the version number, and specifies an existing version it is "scheduled before".  So adding 3.4.1, I would assume it it scheduled before 3.5.  However "before" refers to the vertical layout of versions, not the time at which releases are made.

