While most text custom fields do work with wildcards (* at the end), calculated custom fields don't seem to. As evidence I'm taking the 'Company' calculated custom field from the [toolkit|http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRAEXT/JIRA+Toolkit].

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-8333].
  {panel}

It would be nice if one of the steps of a move operation was to add a comment.  Currently, we have to do a comment and move as two seperate steps, which generates two seperate emails.  Besides, seems like this is how most other workflow actions and operations act, so it seems to make sense.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-8327].
  {panel}

Improve startup message to include URL to start JIRA

Currently the {{ConsistencyCheckImpl}} prints out a message that looks like

{code}
**********************************************************************************************************************
JIRA 3.4-beta1 build: 105 (Enterprise Edition) successfully started. You can now access JIRA through your web browser.
**********************************************************************************************************************
{code}

In an ideal world you'd also want to have the URL like {{http://localhost:8080/jira/}} so that novices know where to go from there
